</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[160,1155,1563,1728]" lastBlockId="12.[160,1155,1596,1690]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="2850" pageId="11" pageNumber="2849">
Detailed examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[494,544,1599,1624]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2849">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tikader &amp; Gajbe" authorityYear="1976" box="[588,776,1599,1624]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="2849" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meghalayensis">
<emphasis box="[588,776,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2849">S. meghalayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed that it lacks diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[288,385,1634,1659]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="2849" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[288,385,1634,1659]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2849">Sergiolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see the previous paragraph on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[755,978,1634,1659]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="2849" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamhetaghatensis">
<emphasis box="[755,978,1634,1659]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2849">H. lamhetaghatensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), but instead, it has all of the diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kamura" authorityYear="1992" box="[569,648,1668,1693]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Hitobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="2849" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[569,648,1668,1693]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2849">Hitobia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as in the case of previous species (compare 
<figureCitation box="[160,256,1703,1728]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="10.[160,225,1690,1713]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,495,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-81@10.[163,1153,492,1658]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 5. Hitobia meghalayensis comb. nov., female holotype of Sergiolus meghalayensis (NZC-ZSI -5045/18). (a) habitus, dorsal view. (b) eyes, dorsal view. (c) epigyne, ventral view. (d) same, dorsal view. (e) label from type bottle. Scale bars a = 2 mm; b = 0.5 mm; c–d = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405199" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405199/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="2849">Figure 5</figureCitation>
(b–d) with 
<bibRefCitation author="Kamura T" box="[384,535,1703,1728]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2849" pagination="119 - 132" refId="ref7382" refString="Kamura T. 1992. Two new genera of the family Gnaphosidae (Araneae) from Japan. Acta Arachnologica. 41: 119 - 132. doi: 10.2476 / asjaa. 41.119." type="journal article" year="1992">Kamura 1992</bibRefCitation>
, figs 11, 16, 20, 25). Moreover, this species has three cheliceral promarginal and one retromarginal teeth (
<bibRefCitation author="Tikader BK &amp; Gajbe UA" box="[764,1039,1596,1621]" pageId="12" pageNumber="2850" pagination="185 - 191" refId="ref8113" refString="Tikader BK, Gajbe UA. 1976. On some new species of spiders of the genus Sergiolus Simon from India (family: Gnaphosidae). Proc Indian Acad Sci. 84: 185 - 191." type="journal article" year="1976">Tikader and Gajbe 1976</bibRefCitation>
), which is another diagnostic feature of 
<taxonomicName box="[499,667,1631,1656]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Hitobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="2850" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[499,578,1631,1656]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="2850">Hitobia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kamura T" box="[681,832,1631,1656]" pageId="12" pageNumber="2850" pagination="119 - 132" refId="ref7382" refString="Kamura T. 1992. Two new genera of the family Gnaphosidae (Araneae) from Japan. Acta Arachnologica. 41: 119 - 132. doi: 10.2476 / asjaa. 41.119." type="journal article" year="1992">Kamura 1992</bibRefCitation>
, figs 12, 21). Based on these observations, we propose to transfer 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tikader &amp; Gajbe" authorityYear="1976" box="[580,766,1665,1690]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="2850" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meghalayensis">
<emphasis box="[580,766,1665,1690]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="2850">S. meghalayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kamura" authorityYear="1992" box="[804,883,1665,1690]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Hitobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="2850" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[804,883,1665,1690]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="2850">Hitobia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
