<emphasis box="[296,490,178,203]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">H. meghalayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[501,630,178,203]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are closely related to the females of 
<taxonomicName authority="Song, Zhu &amp; Zhang, 2004" authorityName="Song, Zhu &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2004" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Hitobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="menglong">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Hitobia menglong</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Song DX &amp; Zhu MS &amp; Zhang F" box="[276,555,212,237]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851" pagination="362" refId="ref8058" refString="Song DX, Zhu MS, Zhang F. 2004. Fauna Sinica: Invertebrata. Vol. 39, Arachnida: Araneae: Gnaphosidae. Beijing: Science Press; p. 362." type="book chapter" year="2004">Song, Zhu &amp; Zhang, 2004</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as both share inverted droplet-shaped spermathecae, but can be separated from the latter by W-shaped posterior epigynal margin (which is crescent-like in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Song, Zhu &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2004" box="[336,476,282,307]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Hitobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="menglong">
<emphasis box="[336,476,282,307]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">H. menglong</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (compare 
<figureCitation box="[605,698,282,307]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="10.[160,225,1690,1713]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,495,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-81@10.[163,1153,492,1658]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 5. Hitobia meghalayensis comb. nov., female holotype of Sergiolus meghalayensis (NZC-ZSI -5045/18). (a) habitus, dorsal view. (b) eyes, dorsal view. (c) epigyne, ventral view. (d) same, dorsal view. (e) label from type bottle. Scale bars a = 2 mm; b = 0.5 mm; c–d = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405199" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405199/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Figure 5</figureCitation>
(c–d) with 
<bibRefCitation author="Song DX &amp; Zhu MS &amp; Zhang F" box="[817,999,282,307]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851" pagination="362" refId="ref8058" refString="Song DX, Zhu MS, Zhang F. 2004. Fauna Sinica: Invertebrata. Vol. 39, Arachnida: Araneae: Gnaphosidae. Beijing: Science Press; p. 362." type="book chapter" year="2004">Song et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
, figs 87H–I).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[160,1156,350,653]" box="[160,478,350,376]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,478,350,376]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Supplementary description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[160,1156,350,653]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">
<emphasis box="[160,238,386,411]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Female</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[256,360,386,411]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<figureCitation box="[375,472,386,411]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="10.[160,225,1690,1713]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,495,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-81@10.[163,1153,492,1658]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 5. Hitobia meghalayensis comb. nov., female holotype of Sergiolus meghalayensis (NZC-ZSI -5045/18). (a) habitus, dorsal view. (b) eyes, dorsal view. (c) epigyne, ventral view. (d) same, dorsal view. (e) label from type bottle. Scale bars a = 2 mm; b = 0.5 mm; c–d = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405199" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405199/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Figure 5</figureCitation>
(a–b)). Body length 9.78. Prosoma length 3.73, width 2.74. Opisthosoma length 6.05, width 3.64. Eye sizes and interdistances: ALE 0.12. AME 0.10. PLE 0.13. PME 0.11; AME–AME 0.09. AME–PME 0.18. PME–PLE 0.15. PME–PME 0.16. Length of chelicerae 1.12. Clypeus height at ALEs 0.11, at AMEs 0.16. 
<emphasis box="[888,973,490,515]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Epigyne</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[991,1088,490,515]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="10.[160,225,1690,1713]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,495,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-81@10.[163,1153,492,1658]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 5. Hitobia meghalayensis comb. nov., female holotype of Sergiolus meghalayensis (NZC-ZSI -5045/18). (a) habitus, dorsal view. (b) eyes, dorsal view. (c) epigyne, ventral view. (d) same, dorsal view. (e) label from type bottle. Scale bars a = 2 mm; b = 0.5 mm; c–d = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405199" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405199/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Figure 5</figureCitation>
(c–d)): epigynal plate sclerotised, roughly diamond-shaped, with diagonally oriented posterolateral sclerotised margins and W-shaped posterior epigynal margin (
<figureCitation box="[1014,1115,559,584]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="10.[160,225,1690,1713]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,495,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-81@10.[163,1153,492,1658]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 5. Hitobia meghalayensis comb. nov., female holotype of Sergiolus meghalayensis (NZC-ZSI -5045/18). (a) habitus, dorsal view. (b) eyes, dorsal view. (c) epigyne, ventral view. (d) same, dorsal view. (e) label from type bottle. Scale bars a = 2 mm; b = 0.5 mm; c–d = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405199" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405199/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Figure 5</figureCitation>
(c)). Spermathecae large sac-like (
<figureCitation box="[489,582,594,619]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="10.[160,225,1690,1713]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,495,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-81@10.[163,1153,492,1658]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 5. Hitobia meghalayensis comb. nov., female holotype of Sergiolus meghalayensis (NZC-ZSI -5045/18). (a) habitus, dorsal view. (b) eyes, dorsal view. (c) epigyne, ventral view. (d) same, dorsal view. (e) label from type bottle. Scale bars a = 2 mm; b = 0.5 mm; c–d = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405199" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405199/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Figure 5</figureCitation>
(d)). Fertilisation ducts narrow, diverging.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[160,1156,350,653]" box="[192,373,628,653]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">
<emphasis box="[192,245,628,653]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
